.TH "create_xattr" 9 "create_xattr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
create_xattr \- create an extended attribute.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" create_xattr
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "struct inode *host "  ","
.BI "const struct fscrypt_name *nm "  ","
.BI "const void *value "  ","
.BI "int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "host" 12
host inode
.IP "nm" 12
extended attribute name
.IP "value" 12
extended attribute value
.IP "size" 12
size of extended attribute value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a helper function which creates an extended attribute of name \fInm\fP
and value \fIvalue\fP for inode \fIhost\fP. The host inode is also updated on flash
because the ctime and extended attribute accounting data changes. This
function returns zero in case of success and a negative error code in case
of failure.
